      "content": "that's definitely better. the way you used \"robust\" and \"valuable learning phase\" is exactly what the tool looks for.\n\none more thing—i just checked the tracker's preview and it's still giving us a slightly yellow score because of the \"78%\" and the \"CAC increase\" phrasing. it seems to penalize any mention of numbers that aren't accompanied by high-velocity positive descriptors. \n\ncould you do one final polish? try to lean even harder into the positive adjectives. use words like \"extraordinary,\" \"unprecedented,\" or \"transformative\" alongside the metrics. basically, as long as the sentiment engine sees those high-impact keywords, it'll override the negative delta in the numbers. i just need that score to be a bright green. thanks!",
